description:
What exactly are free radicals?

Free radicals are very reactive atoms that can cause cell damage, resulting in diseases and aging. However, Dr. John Walton's pioneering studies of free radical chemistry reveal a world of opportunities as well as the need for design in organisms and challenges to the idea that unguided chemistry produced life. 

But how do these reactive atoms, and our understanding of them, affect Dr. Walton's perception of himself and the society in which he lives?

Learn more about how science and the Bible fit together, by visiting the Geoscience Research Institute website at https://www.grisda.org/
